gas.set(T=900. 0,P=1.0e5, X=&#39;CH4:mole_ CH4,O2:mole_ O2,N2:mole_ N2&#39;)

Right now, I just compute the new stoichiometry (according to my phi) 
and then modify the value in the set command. This is not a big deal, 
but it takes some time when you want to do the calculation for many 
conditions. Anatoli&#39;s approach is a very good idea. However, it still 
requires the mole fractions to be given as strings, which do not 
support arithmetic operations. Thank you both again for your interest 
and help. Best Regards, Peter

